title: Flagg scores ACC freshman-record 42 in Duke win
description: Cooper Flagg scored an ACC freshman-record 42 points to help No. 4 Duke hold off Notre Dame 86-78 on Saturday.

title: Auburn's Broome sprains ankle, will undergo MRI
description: Auburn star Johni Broome left Saturday's 66-63 win at South Carolina with a "significant sprain" of his left ankle, Bruce Pearl said.
author: Jeff Borzello

title: 'Nobody gave them a chance' - Plymouth make 'history' with upset
description: Plymouth Argyle interim boss Kevin Nancekivell hopes their win at Brentford will help put his side's season back on track.

title: Man City put eight past Salford to progress to fourth round
description: Watch highlights as Jack Grealish scores his first goal in over a year and James McAtee scores a second-half hat-trick as Manchester City surge to their biggest win since January 2019 to knock League Two Salford out of the FA Cup.

title: Simpson stops Woodall in emotional title victory
description: Callum Simpson halted Steed Woodall to defend his British and Commonwealth super-middleweight titles on an emotional night in Sheffield.

title: Everton confirm reappointment of Moyes as manager
description: Everton have confirmed the return of David Moyes as their new manager.

title: Steelers-Ravens live updates: AFC North rivals clash for 3rd time this season
description: Pittsburgh and Baltimore split their regular-season meetings, with each team winning at home. Who will come out on top of this wild-card game when it matters most?
author: Yahoo Sports

title: UCLA's Mick Cronin ejected from 79-61 loss to Maryland after arguing with officials
description: With five minutes left in the game, Cronin was given a technical and ejected after furiously contesting what he thought was a missed call.
author: Yahoo Sports
